        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-29T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="839" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.936/9–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            state</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-30T09:00:00+08:00">September 30, 1949—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 1—9:10 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 1150. Reference telCan 704, September 28, repeated Taipei 344. We made
                    almost identical verbal explanation to Foreign Office September 23. Foreign
                    Office apparently satisfied.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Taipei 178.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
